args: And yet my lonely rain...never ends.
In a lawless area ruled by a band of brigands,\nthe prince and his friends have taken on a request\nfrom the town to quell the larcenous looters.
Sweet blue hell! Looks like the\nend'a the line for us...
We got ya cornered, ya dogs! Yer days\nof lootin' and pillagin' are over!
If you hope for mercy from us, you will\nagree to return all you have stolen.
Looks like YER the idiot blokes\nwhat got cornered!
Look out, boss! It's a trap!
Time to take out the trash, boys...\nand make it HURT!
W-wait! Just hear me out here, yeah?
I gots me a sick mum, so I does!\nOnly turned cutpurse what so I could\npay the sawbones to look after her!
If I die here, she'll die too!\nSo just lemme go, yeah? I promise to\nbe good after this—I PINKY promise!
Hold it! I don't know who you are,\nbut I'll not stand by and permit you\nto kill a man who seeks to surrender.
*snort* My stories are so good, I ought\ngo write me a novel. Later, suckers!
Oh, I agree: There is naught uglier in life\nthan spinning cowardly deceit in order\nto make good one's escape.
All of you are ugly, too.
Maybe she's right—lettin' a chump like\nthat get away ain't exactly our finest hour.
Still, not sure ya really need to be\ngoin' around callin' folks ugly.
Your ugliness is why I need\nto come with you.
I am very confused right now.\nAlso, who even ARE you?
Linnea—and you are the seventh scion.
I've been looking for you.\nTake me with you.
Er, and WHY do you want to\ncome with us, exactly?
The rigors of the battlefield...\nKill or be killed...\nIt is where people show their true selves.
That's why I'm coming with you:\nI want to fight with you.
I want to see your ugly side.
Ya ask me, boss, this whole plan is ten\npounds'a bullplop in a five-pound sack.
I know ya love invitin' weirdos to hang\nout with us, but I don't see you and her\never comin' to a meetin'a the minds.
No, you're right.\nBut I can't help worrying for her...
Well, Your Highness? What shall we do?
...We'll bring her along. Who knows what\nmight happen if we just leave her here.
Ya sure, boss? I mean, this lady ain't just\nan oddball—she's the ODDEST ball.
What could cause a woman to undertake\nsomething so twisted as a search for the\nultimate ugliness within humanity?
It's a good question, but I feel confident\nshe'll tell us the answer in time.
I mean, there must be SOME reason\nshe's like this...
